te","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,520],"id":"861ae31c-f929-49c8-9f57-2955883605c6","name":"Note: Draft with AI Writer"},{"parameters":{"content":"### OpenAI Writer Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `gpt-4o-mini`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Draft with AI Writer** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenAI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,1090],"id":"7374fd9a-8f3b-d24f-2020-5cbffa81e58f","name":"Note: OpenAI Writer Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Refine with AI Editor\n\nSingle fixed LLM step (no tool choice) — cheaper and more predictable than an agent.\n\nPorts: ①→ Publish Draft to WordPress · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1533,520],"id":"9d6c1966-75be-1e56-609e-077d5a76fe72","name":"Note: Refine with AI Editor"},{"parameters":{"content":"### OpenAI Editor Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `gpt-4o-mini`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Refine with AI Editor** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenAI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1776,1090],"id":"9e6cc918-a409-eca2-98d5-aab446ee79cc","name":"Note: OpenAI Editor Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Publish Draft to WordPress\n\nwordpress — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Save Execution Metadata · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 WordPress credentials","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2100,520],"id":"c7b8146d-7523-8ac1-f3ad-1d831ba05f01","name":"Note: Publish Draft to WordPress"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty content","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2424,520],"id":"15709e58-5629-a1ce-67f3-576966a8d612","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty content\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2748,520],"id":"143c6683-6c62-730f-6b7d-155bda33cdda","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty content"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 50 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3072,520],"id":"08a67818-535a-0a35-ec02-c139c269d4ab","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3396,520],"id":"342cc0fb-7e79-7453-5fd8-af50203e9dd7","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Airtable)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3720,520],"id":"a3a0ad36-0abf-fbab-f4bc-6a46871a7ba3","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Airtable)\n\nairtable — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Airtable PAT","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4044,520],"id":"23e7b0b2-3383-030c-8914-fe9147f3c359","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Airtable)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4368,520],"id":"1e086e28-55ee-1d43-7497-2fb45f9a8d84","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3720,1540],"id":"ffaf4ccd-20ec-42f8-50b0-ac9f980039fe","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4044,1540],"id":"51630a89-8482-15a9-fa6d-c506488b5ec9","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Schedule social posts with Airtable and WordPress 24/7\n\n**Pattern:** Social Scheduler · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nSchedule social posts with Airtable and WordPress 24/7. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual listening is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Stamp & Shape Post → Payload Valid? → Build the Brief → Draft with AI Writer → Refine with AI Editor → Publish Draft to WordPress → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to social scheduler without manual effort\n- Anyone automating listening in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Airtable PAT; OpenAI API key; Slack OAuth2; WordPress credentials.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"63dea8a5-b9c3-9f1a-24f0-27e47fbfe2dc","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-20],"id":"60f5a601-8367-bd79-af35-d6be6463c1b1","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-20],"id":"111c4c4c-356c-e733-8c69-654fd8435d38","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your listening process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-20],"id":"69e935d1-5ee4-91e9-f0ad-96e3991aaac2","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Hourly Schedule":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp & Shape Post","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp & Shape Post":{"main":[[{"node":"Payload Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Payload Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Build the Brief","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Record Rejected Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Build the Brief":{"main":[[{"node":"Draft with AI Writer","type":"main","index":0}]]},"OpenAI Writer Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Draft with AI Writer","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Draft with AI Writer":{"main":[[{"node":"Refine with AI Editor","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"OpenAI Editor Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Refine with AI Editor","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Refine with AI Editor":{"main":[[{"node":"Publish Draft to WordPress","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Publish Draft to WordPress":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty content","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty content":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Airtable)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Airtable)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"a85e78e7-8d3d-49e6-beb8-4eb08766a308","id":"FDX06987"}